nerator.Feature.class);\\n        assertThat(factory.getFormatReadFeatureType()).isEqualTo(CBORParser.Feature.class);\\n        assertThat(copied.isEnabled(CBORGenerator.Feature.WRITE_TYPE_HEADER)).isTrue();\\n        assertThat(copied.isEnabled(CBORGenerator.Feature.WRITE_MINIMAL_INTS)).isFalse();\\n\\n        CBORMapper mapper = CBORMapper.builder(copied).build();\\n        byte[] encoded = mapper.writeValueAsBytes(Map.of(\\\"answer\\\", 42));\\n        JsonNode decoded = mapper.readTree(encoded);\\n\\n        assertThat(Arrays.copyOf(encoded, 3)).containsExactly((byte) 0xD9, (byte) 0xD9, (byte) 0xF7);\\n        assertThat(decoded.path(\\\"answer\\\").asInt()).isEqualTo(42);\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1780694141389}]}\n880:[thinking] **Checking Gradle status**\n882:[thinking] It seems like the initial Gradle error might indicate that no changes are needed, which is interesting. I'm wondering if the task was generated after the fix was made. Should I deliver a \"no changes necessary\" message? They likely want me to focus on fixing the current test, possibly from version 2.14.3. I think I'll take a moment to check the global git status to ensure everything is in order.\n886:[tool-call] delta {\"command\":\"git status --short\"}\n887:[tool-call] end id=call_R2ldpeoJyLo1122H5k769VrN|fc_0fd98faaac316379016a233c81ffe8819697d589b11c554ce5 name=bash args={\"command\": \"git status --short\"}\n888:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Checking Gradle status**\\n\\nIt seems like the initial Gradle error might indicate that no changes are needed, which is interesting. I'm wondering if the task was generated after the fix was made. Should I deliver a \\\"no changes necessary\\\" message? They likely want me to focus on fixing the current test, possibly from version 2.14.3. I think I'll take a moment to check the global git status to ensure everything is in